WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#289: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:234:
+	BUG_ON(drive->dev_flags & IDE_DFLAG_BLOCKED);

BUG() or BUG_ON() should be avoided totally.
Use WARN() and WARN_ON() instead, and handle the "impossible"
error condition as gracefully as possible.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/deprecated.html#bug-and-bug-on

CHECK:COMPARISON_TO_NULL: Comparison to NULL could be written "!best"
#707: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-io.c:947:
+			if (best == NULL ||

Comparisons to NULL in the form (foo == NULL) or (foo != NULL)
are better written as (!foo) and (foo).

CHECK:COMPARISON_TO_NULL: Comparison to NULL could be written "!drive->id"
#1043: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-probe.c:565:
+	if (drive->id == NULL) {

CHECK:MACRO_ARG_PRECEDENCE: Macro argument 'flag' may be better as '(flag)' to avoid precedence issues
#1887: FILE: include/linux/ide.h:843:
+#define ide_devset_get_flag(name, flag) \
+static int get_##name(ide_drive_t *drive) \
+{ \
+	return !!(drive->dev_flags & flag); \
+}

CHECK:MACRO_ARG_REUSE: Macro argument reuse 'flag' - possible side-effects?
#1893: FILE: include/linux/ide.h:849:
+#define ide_devset_set_flag(name, flag) \
+static int set_##name(ide_drive_t *drive, int arg) \
+{ \
+	if (arg) \
+		drive->dev_flags |= flag; \
+	else \
+		drive->dev_flags &= ~flag; \
+	return 0; \
+}

ERROR:MULTISTATEMENT_MACRO_USE_DO_WHILE: Macros with multiple statements should be enclosed in a do - while loop
#1910: FILE: include/linux/ide.h:894:
+#define ide_devset_rw_flag(_name, _field) \
+ide_devset_get_flag(_name, _field); \
+ide_devset_set_flag(_name, _field); \
+IDE_DEVSET(_name, DS_SYNC, get_##_name, set_##_name)

Macros with multiple statements should be enclosed in a
do - while block.  Same should also be the case for macros
starting with `if` to avoid logic defects::

  #define macrofun(a, b, c)                 \
    do {                                    \
            if (a == 5)                     \
                    do_this(b, c);          \
    } while (0)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#macros-enums-and-rtl

